<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Non-Linear Editing" class="currentChild" href="Non-Linear_Editing">Non-Linear Editing</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In video production, a means of editing video clips by storing video images on a <a title="Non-Linear" href="Non-Linear">non-linear</a> storage medium, such as a <a title="Hard Disk" href="Hard_Disk">hard disk</a>, <a title="videodisc" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/videodisc">videodisc</a>, etc., and editing them together simply by indicating new <a title="edit in/out point" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/edit_in/out_point">edit in/out point</a>s and clip orders. In contrast, <a title="Linear Editing" href="Linear_Editing">linear editing</a> requires all clips to be physically placed in the correct order. 
</p>
